S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureCatalogue.S100FC:name: Feature catalog for S-999
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureCatalogue.S100FC:scope: Ocean, Coastal, Ports and Harbors. Excludes Inland waters.

S100CI:contactInfo.S100CI:contactInstructions: see UpdatedInformation for an example naming multiple features in one feature binding. This file is intended only to demonstrate the possibilities for FC structure. Features, attributes, associations, visibility, etc., may not correspond to the GI Registry or to any actual product. There ought to be in a comment field for the feature catalog header.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Call Sign
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The designated call-sign of a station (radio station, radar station, pilot, ...).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Authority
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The type of person, government agency or organisation granted powers of managing or controlling access to and/or activity in an area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Border Control
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The administration to prevent or detect and prosecute violations of rules and regulations at international boundaries.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Police
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The department of government, or civil force, charged with maintaining public order.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Port
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Person or corporation, owners of, or entrusted with or invested with the power of managing a port. May be called a Harbour Board, Port Trust, Port Commission, Harbour Commission, Marine Department.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Immigration
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The authority controlling people entering a country.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Health
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The authority with responsibility for checking the validity of the health declaration of a vessel and for declaring free pratique.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coast Guard
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Organization keeping watch on shipping and coastal waters according to governmental law; normally the authority with responsibility for search and rescue.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Agricultural
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The authority with responsibility for preventing infection of the agriculture of a country and for the protection of the agricultural interests of a country.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Military
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A military authority which provides control of access to or approval for transit through designated areas or airspace.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Private Company
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A private or publicly owned company or commercial enterprise which exercises control of facilities, for example a calibration area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Maritime Police
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A governmental or military force with jurisdiction in territorial waters. Examples could include Gendarmerie Maritime, Carabinierie, and Guardia Civil.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Environmental
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An authority with responsibility for the protection of the environment.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fishery
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An authority with responsibility for the control of fisheries.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Finance
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An authority with responsibility for the control and movement of money.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Maritime
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A national or regional authority charged with administration of maritime affairs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Customs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The agency or establishment for collecting duties, tolls.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Crane
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of machines used for hoisting and moving heavy objects.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Container Crane/Gantry
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A high speed, shore-based crane used in the lift-on/lift-off operation of specially constructed containers.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sheerlegs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tripodal structure used in dockyards and harbours for stepping masts or lifting loads in to and out of vessels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Travelling Crane
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A crane mounted on rails (track) that can move (usually parallel to the wharf face) in order to load and unload cargo vessels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: A-Frame
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A type of crane shaped like the letter 'A'.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Goliath Crane
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A powerful travelling crane mounted on a movable gantry of large span.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Harbour Facility
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of harbour use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: RoRo Terminal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A terminal for roll-on roll-off ferries.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ferry Terminal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A terminal for passenger and vehicle ferries.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fishing Harbour
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A harbour with facilities for fishing boats.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Yacht Harbour/Marina
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A harbour facility for small boats, yachts, etc., where supplies, repairs, and various services are available.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Naval Base
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A centre of operations for naval vessels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Tanker Terminal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A terminal for the bulk handling of liquid cargoes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Passenger Terminal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A terminal for the loading and unloading of passengers.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Shipyard
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place where ships are built or repaired.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Container Terminal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A terminal with facilities to load/unload or store shipping containers.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bulk Terminal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A terminal for the handling of bulk materials such as iron ore, coal, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ship Lift
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A platform powered by synchronous electric motors (for example syncrolift) used to lift vessels (larger than boats) in and out of the water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Straddle Carrier
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A wheeled vehicle designed to lift and carry containers or vessels within its own framework. It is used for moving, and sometimes stacking, shipping containers and vessels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Service Harbour
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A harbour within which the floating equipment (dredges, tugs ...) of harbour services are stationed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pilotage Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The services of a person who directs the movements of a vessel through pilot waters, usually a person who has demonstrated extensive knowledge of channels, aids to navigation, dangers to navigation, etc., in a particular area and is licensed for that area, are available.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Pilot Boarding Place
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of pilot boarding method.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Boarding by Pilot-Cruising Vessel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Pilot boards from a cruising vessel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Boarding by Helicopter
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Pilot boards by helicopter which comes out from the shore.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pilot Comes Out from Shore
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Pilot embarks from a vessel or disembarks on a vessel which comes out from the shore on request.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Preference
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The selection of a first choice compared to other options.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Primary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The preferred first choice used in normal conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Alternate
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The preferred choice in extraordinary conditions.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Restricted Area
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The official legal status of each kind of restricted area defines the kind of restriction(s), for example the restriction for a 'game reserve' may be 'entering prohibited'.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Offshore Safety Zone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The area around an offshore installation within which vessels are prohibited from entering without permission. Special regulations protect installations within a safety zone and vessels of all nationalities are required to respect the zone.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nature Reserve
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tract of land or water managed so as to preserve its flora, fauna, physical features, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bird Sanctuary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place where birds are bred and protected.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Game Reserve
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place where wild animals or birds hunted for sport or food are kept undisturbed for private use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Seal Sanctuary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place where seals are protected.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Degaussing Range
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area, usually about two cables diameter, within which ships' magnetic fields may be measured; sensing instruments and cables are installed on the sea bed in the range and there are cables leading from the range to a control position ashore.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Military Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area controlled by the military in which restrictions may apply.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Historic Wreck Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area around certain wrecks of historical importance to protect the wrecks from unauthorized interference by diving, salvage or deposition (including anchoring).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Navigational Aid Safety Zone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area around a navigational aid which vessels are prohibited from entering.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Minefield
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area laid and maintained with explosive mines for defence or practice purposes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Swimming Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area in which people may swim and therefore vessel movement may be restricted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Waiting Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area reserved for vessels waiting to enter a harbour.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Research Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area where marine research takes place.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dredging Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area where dredging is taking place.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fish Sanctuary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place where fish (including shellfish and crustaceans) are protected.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ecological Reserve
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tract of land managed so as to preserve the relation of plants and living creatures to each other and to their surroundings.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: No Wake Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area in which a vessels' speed must be reduced in order to reduce the size of the wake it produces.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Swinging Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area where vessels turn.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Environmentally Sensitive Sea Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A generic term which may be used to describe a wide range of areas, considered sensitive for a variety of environmental reasons.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Particularly Sensitive Sea Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area that needs special protection through action by IMO because of its significance for regional ecological, socio-economic or scientific reasons and because it may be vulnerable to damage by international shipping activities.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Disengagement Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area near a fairway where vessels can go to clear the way or make an about turn and possibly return to a waiting area when nautical conditions impose it.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Port Security Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area in which defence, law and treaty enforcement, and counter-terrorism activities that fall within the port and maritime domain apply.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coral Sanctuary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place where coral is protected.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Recreation Area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which recreational activities regularly take place and therefore vessel movement may be restricted.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Temporal Variation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: An assessment of the likelihood of change over time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Extreme Event
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indication of the possible impact of a significant event (for example hurricane, earthquake, volcanic eruption, landslide, etc), which is considered likely to have changed the seafloor or landscape significantly.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Likely to Change and Significant Shoaling Expected
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Continuous or frequent change (for example river siltation, sand waves, seasonal storms, ice bergs, etc) that is likely to result in new significant shoaling.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Likely to Change But Significant Shoaling Not Expected
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Continuous or frequent change (for example sand wave shift, seasonal storms, ice bergs, etc) that is not likely to result in new significant shoaling.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Likely to Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Continuous or frequent change to non-bathymetric features (for example river siltation, glacier creep/recession, sand dunes, buoys, marine farms, etc).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unlikely to Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Significant change to the seafloor is not expected.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unassessed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Not having been assessed.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Text
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of completeness of textual information in relation to the source material from which it is derived.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Abstract or Summary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A statement summarizing the important points of a text.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Extract
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An excerpt or excerpts from a text.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Full Text
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The whole text.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Zone of Confidence In Data
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of the zone of confidence in data within an area based on the positional accuracy, survey equipment and coverage.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: See S-57 Appendix A, Chapter 2, Page 2.107 for the full list of ZOC categories.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Zone of Confidence A1
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Positional Accuracy +/- 5 metres; Depth Accuracy 0.5 metre +1% depth; Full area search undertaken. Significant seafloor features detected and depths measured; Controlled, systematic survey, high position and depth accuracy achieved using DGPS or a minimum three high quality lines of position (LOP) and a multibeam, channel or mechanical sweep system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Zone of Confidence A2
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Positional Accuracy +/- 20 metres; Depth Accuracy 1.0 metre + 2% depth; Full area search undertaken. Significant seafloor features detected and depths measured; Controlled, systematic survey achieving position and depth accuracy less than ZOC A1 and using a modern survey echosounder and a sonar or mechanical sweep system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Zone of Confidence B
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Positional Accuracy +/- 50 metres; Depth Accuracy 1.0 metre + 2% depth; Full area search not achieved, uncharted features hazardous to surface navigation are not expected but may exist; Controlled, systematic survey achieving similar depth but lesser position accuracies than ZOCA2, using a modern survey echosounder, but no sonar or mechanical sweep system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Zone of Confidence C
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Positional Accuracy +/- 500 metres; Depth Accuracy 2.0 metre + 5% depth; Full area search not achieved, depth anomalies may be expected; Low accuracy survey or data collected on an opportunity basis such as soundings on passage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Zone of Confidence D
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Positional Accuracy worse than ZOC C; Depth Accuracy worse than ZOC C; Full area search not achieved, large depth anomalies may be expected; Poor quality data or data that cannot be quality assessed due to lack of information.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Zone of Confidence U
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The quality of the bathymetric data has yet to be assessed.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Colour
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The property possessed by an object of producing different sensations on the eye as a result of the way it reflects or emits light.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: White
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The achromatic object colour of greatest lightness characteristically perceived to belong to objects that reflect diffusely nearly all incident energy throughout the visible spectrum.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Black
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The achromatic color of least lightness characteristically perceived to belong to objects that neither reflect nor transmit light.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Red
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A color whose hue resembles that of blood or of the ruby or is that of the long-wave extreme of the visible spectrum.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Green
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Of the color green.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Blue
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A color whose hue is that of the clear sky or that of the portion of the color spectrum lying between green and violet.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Yellow
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A color whose hue resembles that of ripe lemons or sunflowers or is that of the portion of the spectrum lying between green and orange.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Grey
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Of the color grey.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Brown
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any of a group of colors between red and yellow in hue, of medium to low lightness, and of moderate to low saturation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Amber
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A variable color averaging a dark orange yellow.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Violet
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any of a group of colors of reddish-blue hue, low lightness, and medium saturation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Orange
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any of a group of colors that are between red and yellow in hue.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Magenta
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A deep purplish red.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pink
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any of a group of colors bluish red to red in hue, of medium to high lightness, and of low to moderate saturation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Colour Pattern
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A regular repeated design containing more than one colour.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Horizontal Stripes
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Straight bands or stripes of differing colours oriented horizontally.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Vertical Stripes
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Straight bands or stripes of differing colours oriented vertically.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Diagonal Stripes
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Straight bands or stripes of differing colours oriented diagonally (that is, not horizontally or vertically).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Squared
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Often referred to as checker plate, where alternate colours are used to create squares similar to a chess or draught board. The pattern may be straight or diagonal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stripes (Direction Unknown)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Straight bands or stripes of differing colours oriented in an unknown direction.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Border Stripe
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A band or stripe of colour which is displayed around the outer edge of the object, which may also form a border to an inner pattern or plain colour.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Communication Channel
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A channel number assigned to a specific radio frequency, frequencies or frequency band.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The expected input is the specific VHF-Channel. The attribute 'communication channel' encodes the various VHF-channels used for communication.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Condition
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The various conditions of buildings and other constructions.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The default 'condition' should be considered to be completed, undamaged and working normally.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Under Construction
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Being built but not yet capable of function.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ruined
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure in a decayed or deteriorated condition resulting from neglect or disuse, or a damaged structure in need of repair.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Under Reclamation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area of the sea, a lake or the navigable part of a river that is being reclaimed as land, usually by the dumping of earth and other material.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wingless
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A windmill or wind turbine from which the vanes or turbine blades are missing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Planned Construction
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Detailed planning has been completed but construction has not been initiated.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Contact Instructions
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Instructions provided on how to contact a particular person, organisation or service.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Data Assessment
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The categorization of the assessment level of bathymetric data for an area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Assessed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The quality of the bathymetric data has been assessed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Assessed (Oceanic)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The quality of oceanic bathymetric data (depths deeper than 200 metres) has been assessed, however details are not required.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unassessed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Not having been assessed.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date End
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The latest date on which an object (for example a buoy) will be present.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The Date End should be encoded using 4 digits for the calendar year (YYYY), 2 digits for the month (MM) (for example April = 04) and 2 digits for the day (DD). When no specific month and/or day is required/known, indication of the month and/or day is omitted, and replaced with dashes (-). When no specific year is required (that is, the event or date range ends at the same time each year) the following two cases may be considered:- same day each year: ----MMDD- same month each year: ----MM--This conforms to ISO 8601: 2004. Date End indicates the latest date of an event or the end of a date range. It is used to indicate the end of a fixed date range, the end of a periodic date range, or the removal or cancellation of a feature at a specific date in the future.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date Start
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The earliest date on which an object (for example a buoy) will be present.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The Date Start should be encoded using 4 digits for the calendar year (YYYY), 2 digits for the month (MM) (for example April = 04) and 2 digits for the day (DD). When no specific month and/or day is required/known, indication of the month and/or day is omitted, and replaced with dashes (-). When no specific year is required (that is, the event or date range ends at the same time each year) the following two cases may be considered:- same day each year: ----MMDD- same month each year: ----MM--This conforms to ISO 8601: 2004. Date Start indicates the earliest date of an event or the start of a date range. It is used to indicate the start of a fixed date range, the start of a periodic date range, or the deployment or implementation of a feature at a specific date in the future.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Depth Range Maximum Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The maximum (deepest) value of a depth range.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Where the area dries, the value is negative.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Depth Range Minimum Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The minimum (shoalest) value of a depth range.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Where the area dries, the value is negative.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Destination
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The place or general direction to which a vessel is going or directed.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: In addition to a place name of a port, harbour area or terminal, the place could include generalities such as The north-west, or upriver.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Display Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement expressing if a feature name is to be displayed in certain system display settings or not.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Where it is allowable to encode multiple instances of feature name for a single feature instance, only one feature name instance can indicate that the name is to be displayed (display name set to True).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Locator
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The location of a fragment of text or other information in a support file.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Application schemas must describe how the associated file is identified. The associated file will commonly be named in a file reference co-attribute of the same complex attribute. Each DCEG must specify requirements for the format of the associated file and the semantics of file locator. For example, the value of file locator may be an HTML ID in an HTML file, line number in a text file) or a bookmark in a PDF file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Reference
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The file name of an externally referenced text file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Frequency Shore Station Receives
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The shore station receiver frequency.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Examples: 4379.1 kHz becomes 043791; 13162.8 kHz becomes 131628.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Frequency Shore Station Transmits
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The shore station transmitter frequency.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Examples: 4379.1 kHz becomes 043791; 13162.8 kHz becomes 131628.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Full Seafloor Coverage Achieved
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Expression stating if full seafloor coverage has been achieved in the area covered by hydrographic surveys.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Full seafloor coverage achieved applies to both the spatial completeness of feature detection and to the spatial completeness of the measurement of the regular seafloor. The former is further specified by the complex attribute features detected, the latter by the attributes depth range maximum value and depth range minimum value.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Headline
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Words set at the head of a passage or page to introduce or categorize.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Height
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The value of the vertical distance to the highest point of the object, measured from a specified vertical datum.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Height must not be used for floating objects.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Clearance Length
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The length of a feature, such as a lock or basin, which is available for safe navigation. This may, or may not, be the same as the total physical length of the feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Clearance Width
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The width of an object, such as a lock or basin, which is available for safe navigation. This may, or may not, be the same as the total physical width of the object.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Distance Uncertainty
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the horizontal accuracy of horizontal clearances and distances.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The error is assumed to be positive and negative. The plus/minus character must not be encoded.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Ice Factor
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The value of the maximum variation in the vertical clearance of an overhead cable due to an accumulation of ice.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: IMO Adopted
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A defined maritime traffic route that has been adopted as an IMO routeing measure.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: In Dispute
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement that expresses if an area is in a jurisdictional dispute.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: In the Water
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: An indication if the feature is located in or over navigable water.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: A True value is an indication that the feature is to be included in the ECDIS Base Display viewing group.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Language
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The method of human communication, either spoken or written, consisting of the use of words in a structured and conventional way.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The language is encoded by a 3 character code following ISO 639-2/T.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Lifting Capacity
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The specific safe lifting capacity of a feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Linkage
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Location (address) for on-line access using a URL/URI address or similar addressing scheme.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Major Light
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement expressing if a light is considered to be a major light in terms of ECDIS display in a particular area.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Major light is only intended to provide an indication to the ECDIS that the light is considered to be an important light in terms of its display. As such this is a cartographic attribute to aid the compiler in determining the most appropriate display for a light; it is not intended to be used as a formal classification method for lights.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Marks Navigational - System Of
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The system of navigational buoyage a region complies with.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: IALA A
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to the International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA A system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: IALA B
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to the International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA B system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: No System
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids do not conform to any defined system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: CEVNI
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: CEVNI (European Code for Navigation on Inland Waterways) is the European code for rivers, canals land lakes in most of Europe.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Maximum Display Scale
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The largest intended viewing scale for the data.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Maximum Permitted Draught
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The maximum draught of a vessel permitted along a route, in a channel or dock, at a berth, or over a submerged feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Minimum Display Scale
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The smallest intended viewing scale for the data.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: MMSI Code
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The Maritime Mobile Service Identity (MMSI) Code is formed of a series of nine digits which are transmitted over the radio path in order to uniquely identify ship stations, ship earth stations,coast stations, coast earth stations, and group calls. These identities are formed in such a way that the identity or part thereof can be used by telephone and telex subscribers connected to the general telecommunications network principally to call ships automatically.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The individual name of a feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Name of Resource
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Name of the online resource.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Nature of Construction
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The building's primary construction material.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Masonry
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed of stones or bricks, usually quarried, shaped, and mortared.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Concreted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed of concrete, a material made of sand and gravel that is united by cement into a hardened mass used for roads, foundations, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Loose Boulders
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from large stones or blocks of concrete, often placed loosely for protection against waves or water turbulence.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Hard Surfaced
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed with a surface of hard material, usually a term applied to roads surfaced with asphalt or concrete.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unsurfaced
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed with no extra protection, usually a term applied to roads not surfaced with a hard material.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wooden
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from wood.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Metal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from metal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Glass Reinforced Plastic
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from a plastic material strengthened with fibres of glass.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Latticed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure of crossed wooden or metal strips usually arranged to form a diagonal pattern of open spaces between the strips.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Glass
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: [1] Any artificial or natural substance having similar properties and composition, as fused borax, obsidian, or the like. [2] Something made of such a substance, as a windowpane.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Orientation Uncertainty
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the accuracy of a bearing.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Orientation Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The angular distance measured from true north to the major axis of the feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Pictorial Representation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Indicates whether a pictorial representation of the feature is available.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The 'pictorial representation' could be a drawing or a photo. The string encodes the file name of an external graphic file (pixel/vector).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Pilot Movement
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of pilot activity by arrival, departure, or change of pilot. It may also describe the place where the pilot's advice begins, ends, or is transferred to a different pilot.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Embarkation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The place where vessels not being navigated according to a pilots instructions pick up a pilot while in transit from sea to a port or constricted waters for future navigation under pilot instructions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Disembarkation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The place where vessels being navigated under a pilots instructions in transit from sea to a port or constricted waters drop the pilot and proceed without being subject to pilot instructions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pilot Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The place where vessels being navigated under a pilots instructions drop off the pilot and pick up a different pilot for future navigation under pilots instructions.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Product
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The various substances which are transported, stored or exploited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Oil
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A thick, slippery liquid that will not dissolve in water, usually petroleum based in the context of storage tanks.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Gas
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A substance with particles that can move freely, usually a fuel substance in the context of storage tanks.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A colourless, odourless, tasteless liquid that is a compound of hydrogen and oxygen.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A general term for rock and rock fragments ranging in size from pebbles and gravel to boulders or large rock masses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A hard black mineral that is burned as fuel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ore
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A solid rock or mineral from which metal is obtained.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Chemicals
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any substance obtained by or used in a chemical process.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Drinking Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Water that is suitable for human consumption.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Milk
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A white fluid secreted by female mammals as food for their young.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bauxite
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mineral from which aluminum is obtained.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coke
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A solid substance obtained after gas and tar have been extracted from coal, used as a fuel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Iron Ingots
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An oblong lump of cast iron metal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Salt
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Sodium chloride obtained from mines or by the evaporation of sea water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sand
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Loose material consisting of small but easily distinguishable, separate grains, between 0.0625 and 2.000 millimetres in diameter.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Timber
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Wood prepared for use in building or carpentry.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sawdust/Wood Chips
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Powdery fragments of wood made in sawing timber or coarse chips produced for use in manufacturing pressed board.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Scrap Metal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Discarded metal suitable for being reprocessed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Liquefied Natural Gas
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Natural gas that has been liquefied for ease of transport by cooling the gas to -162 Celsius.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Liquefied Petroleum Gas
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A compressed gas consisting of flammable light hydrocarbons and derived from petroleum.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wine
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The fermented juice of grapes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cement
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A substance made of powdered lime and clay, mixed with water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Grain
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A small hard seed, especially that of any cereal plant such as wheat, rice, corn, rye etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Electricity
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Electric charge or current.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ice
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The solid form of water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Clay
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (Particles of less than 0.002mm); stiff, sticky earth that becomes hard when baked.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Quality of Vertical Measurement
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The reliability of the value of a sounding.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Depth Known
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth from the chart datum to the seabed (or to the top of a drying feature) is known.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Depth or Least Depth Unknown
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth from chart datum to the seabed, or the shoalest depth of the feature is unknown.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Doubtful Sounding
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A depth that may be less than indicated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unreliable Sounding
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A depth that is considered to be an unreliable value.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Least Depth Known
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The shoalest depth over a feature is of known value.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Least Depth Unknown, Safe Clearance at Value Shown
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The least depth over a feature is unknown, but there is considered to be safe clearance at this depth.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Value Reported (Not Surveyed)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Depth value obtained from a report, but not fully surveyed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Value Reported (Not Confirmed)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Depth value obtained from a report, which it has not been possible to confirm.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Maintained Depth
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth at which a channel is kept by human influence, usually by dredging.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Not Regularly Maintained
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Depths may be altered by human influence, but will not be routinely maintained.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Radar Conspicuous
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A feature which returns a strong radar echo.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Radius
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The vector extending from the centre to the periphery of a circular or spherical object.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Reported Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The date that the item was observed, done, or investigated.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Restriction
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The official legal statute of each kind of restricted area.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Defines the kind of restriction(s), for example, the restriction for 'a game preserve' may be 'entry prohibited', the restriction for an 'anchoring prohibition' is 'anchoring prohibited'. The complete information about the restriction(s), actually held in handbooks or other publications, may be encoded using an Information type.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Anchoring Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which anchoring is not permitted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Anchoring Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specified area designated by appropriate authority, within which anchoring is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fishing Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which fishing is not permitted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fishing Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specified area designated by appropriate authority, within which fishing is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Trawling Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which trawling is not permitted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Trawling Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specified area designated by appropriate authority, within which trawling is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Entry Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which navigation and/or anchoring is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Entry Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specified area designated by appropriate authority, within which navigation is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dredging Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which dredging is not permitted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dredging Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specified area designated by appropriate authority, within which dredging is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Diving Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which diving is not permitted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Diving Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specified area designated by appropriate authority, within which diving is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: No Wake
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Mariners must adjust the speed of their vessels to reduce the wave or wash which may cause erosion or disturb moored vessels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Area To Be Avoided
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An IMO declared routeing measure comprising an area within defined limits in which either navigation is particularly hazardous or it is exceptionally important to avoid casualties and which should be avoided by all ships, or certain classes of ships.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Construction Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The erection of permanent or temporary fixed structures or artificial islands is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Discharging Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which discharging or dumping is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Discharging Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specified area designated by an appropriate authority, within which discharging or dumping is restricted in accordance with specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Industrial or Mineral Exploration/Development Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which industrial or mineral exploration and development are prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Industrial or Mineral Exploration/Development Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specified area designated by an appropriate authority, within which industrial or mineral exploration and development is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Drilling Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which excavating a hole on the sea-bottom with a drill is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Drilling Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specified area designated by an appropriate authority, within which excavating a hole on the sea-bottom with a drill is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Removal of Historical Artefacts Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which the removal of historical artefacts is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cargo Transhipment (Lightening) Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area in which cargo transhipment (lightening) is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dragging Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area in which the dragging of anything along the bottom, e.g. bottom trawling, is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stopping Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area in which a vessel is prohibited from stopping.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Landing Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area in which landing is prohibited.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Speed Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which speed is restricted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Swimming Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area in which swimming is prohibited.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Scale Minimum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The minimum scale at which the feature may be used for example for ECDIS presentation.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The modulus of the scale is indicated, that is 1:1 250 000 is encoded as 1250000.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Status
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The condition of an object at a given instant in time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Permanent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Intended to last or function indefinitely.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Occasional
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Acting on special occasions; happening irregularly.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Recommended
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Presented as worthy of confidence, acceptance, use, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Not in Use
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Use has ceased, but the facility still exists intact; disused.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Periodic/Intermittent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Recurring at intervals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Reserved
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Set apart for some specific use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Temporary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Meant to last only for a time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Private
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Administered by an individual or corporation, rather than a State or a public body.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mandatory
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Compulsory; enforced.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Extinguished
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: No longer lit.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Illuminated
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Lit by floodlights, strip lights, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Historic
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Famous in history; of historical interest.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Public
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Belonging to, available to, used or shared by, the community as a whole and not restricted to private use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Synchronized
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Occur at a time, coincide in point of time, be contemporary or simultaneous.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Watched
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Looked at or observed over a period of time especially so as to be aware of any movement or change.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unwatched
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Usually automatic in operation, without any permanently-stationed personnel to superintend it.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Existence Doubtful
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A feature that has been reported but has not been definitely determined to exist.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoyed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Marked by buoys.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Telecommunication Identifier
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: An identifier, such as words, numbers, letters, symbols, or any combination of those used to establish a contact to a particular person, organisation or service.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Telecommunication Service
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of methods of communication over a distance by electrical, electronic, or electromagnetic means.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Voice
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The transfer or exchange of information by using sounds that are being made by mouth and throat when speaking.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Facsimile
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A system of transmitting and reproducing graphic matter (as printing or still pictures) by means of signals sent over telephone lines.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: SMS
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Short Message Service is a form of text messaging communication on phones and mobile phones.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Data
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A representation of facts, concepts or instructions in a formalised manner suitable for communication, interpretation or processing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Streamed Data
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Data that is constantly received by and presented to an end-user while being delivered by a provider.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Telex
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A system of communication in which messages are sent over long distances by using a telephone system and are printed by using a special machine (called a teletypewriter).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Telegraph
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An apparatus, system or process for communication at a distance by electric transmission over wire.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Email
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Messages and other data exchanged between individuals using computers in a network.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Text
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A non-formatted digital text string.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Should be used, for example, to hold the information that is for short cautionary or explanatory notes. Therefore, text populated in text must not exceed 300 characters. Text may be in English, or in a national language. No formatting of text is possible within text. If formatted text, or text strings exceeding 300 characters, is required, then an alternate concept should be used.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Uncertainty Fixed
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the fixed horizontal or vertical accuracy component for positions, depths, heights, vertical distances and vertical clearances.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Uncertainty Variable Factor
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The factor to be applied to the variable component of an uncertainty equation so as to provide the best estimate of the variable horizontal or vertical accuracy component for positions, depths, heights, vertical distances and vertical clearances.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Clearance Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The vertical clearance measured from the horizontal plane towards the feature overhead.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Datum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The reference level used for expressing the vertical measurements of points on the earth's surface. Also called datum level, reference plane, levelling datum, datum for sounding reduction, datum for heights.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the low waters of spring tides. This level is used as a tidal datum in some areas. Also called spring low water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Lower Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of lower low water springs at a place.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Sea Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the surface of the sea at a tide station for all stages of the tide over a 19-year period, usually determined from hourly height readings measured from a fixed predetermined reference level.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lowest Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level conforming to the lowest tide observed at a place, or some what lower.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of all low waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lowest Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level conforming to the lowest water level observed at a place at spring tides during a period of time shorter than 19 years.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Low Water Springs (MLWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Indian Spring Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary tidal datum approximating the level of the mean of the lower low water at spring tides. It was first used in waters surrounding India.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, approximating that of mean low water springs (MLWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Lowest Astronomical Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Lowest Astronomical Tide (LAT).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nearly Lowest Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level approximating the lowest water level observed at a place, usually equivalent to the Indian Spring Low Water (ISLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Lower Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the lower low waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The lowest level reached at a place by the water surface in one oscillation. Also called low tide.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Low Water (MLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Lower Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Lower Low Water (MLLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of all high waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean High Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the high waters of spring tides. Also called spring high water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The highest level reached at a place by the water surface in one oscillation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Sea Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Sea Level (MSL).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: High Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, approximating that of mean high water springs (MHWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Higher High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of higher high waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Equinoctial Spring Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The level of low water springs near the time of an equinox.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lowest Astronomical Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The lowest tide level which can be predicted to occur under average meteorological conditions and under any combination of astronomical conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Local Datum
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary datum defined by a local harbour authority, from which levels and tidal heights are measured by this authority.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: International Great Lakes Datum 1985
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A vertical reference system with its zero based on the mean water level at Rimouski/Pointe-au-Pere, Quebec, over the period 1970 to 1988.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Water Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average of all hourly water levels over the available period of record.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lower Low Water Large Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average of the lowest low waters, one from each of 19 years of observations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Higher High Water Large Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average of the highest high waters, one from each of 19 years of observations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nearly Highest High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level approximating the highest water level observed at a place, usually equivalent to the high water springs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Highest Astronomical Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The highest tidal level which can be predicted to occur under average meteorological conditions and under any combination of astronomical conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Baltic Sea Chart Datum 2000
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The datum refers to each Baltic country's realization of the European Vertical Reference System (EVRS) with land-uplift epoch 2000, which is connected to the Normaal Amsterdams Peil (NAP).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Length
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The total vertical length of a feature.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: For floating objects: the vertical distance from the surface of water to the highest point of that object. For fixed objects: the vertical distance from seabed or ground to the highest point of that object. For objects on top of other objects: the vertical distance from the lowest to the highest point of that object. Vertical length measurements do not require a datum.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Visual Prominence
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The extent to which a feature, either natural or artificial, is visible from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Visually Conspicuous
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Term applied to a feature either natural or artificial which is distinctly and notably visible from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Not Visually Conspicuous
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An object that may be visible from seaward, but cannot be used as a fixing mark and is not conspicuous.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Prominent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Objects which are easily identifiable, but do not justify being classed as conspicuous.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Feature Name
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Provides the name of an entity, defines the national language of the name, and provides the option to display the name at various system display settings.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Fixed Date Range
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: An active period of a single fixed event or occurrence, as the date range between discrete start and end dates.
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Dates must be encoded in the format YYYYMMDD; using 4 digits for the calendar year (YYYY) and, optionally, 2 digits for the month (MM) (for example April = 04) and 2 digits for the day (DD). When no specific month and/or day is required/known, the values are replaced with dashes (-). The date range of a recurring event or occurrence must be encoded using periodicDateRange.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Frequency Pair
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: A pair of frequencies for transmitting and receiving radio signals. The shore station transmits and receives on the frequencies indicated.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Position Uncertainty
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the accuracy of a position.
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The expected input is the maximum of the two-dimensional error. The error is assumed to be positive and negative.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Information
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Textual information about the feature. The information may be provided as a string of text or as a file name of a single external text file that contains the text.
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:remarks: At least one of the sub-attributes file reference or text must be populated.The sub-attribute file reference is generally used for long text strings or those that require formatting, however, there is no restriction on the type of text (except for lexical level) that can be held in files referenced by sub-attribute file reference.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Online Resource
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Information about online sources from which a resource or data can be obtained.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Orientation
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: (1) The angular distance measured from true north to the major axis of the feature. (2) In ECDIS, the mode in which information on the ECDIS is being presented. Typical modes include: north-up - as shown on a nautical chart, north is at the top of the display; Ships head-up - based on the actual heading of the ship, (e.g. Ships gyrocompass); course-up display - based on the course or route being taken.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Periodic Date Range
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The active period of a recurring event or occurrence.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Survey Date Range
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The complex attribute describes the period of the hydrographic survey, as the time between its sub-attributes.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Telecommunications
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: A means or channel of communicating at a distance by electrical or electromagnetic means such as telegraphy, telephony, or broadcasting.
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:remarks: If no value is populated for the sub-attribute telecommunication service, this means the service is by voice communication. If no value is populated for the sub-attribute telecommunication carrier, this means the service is by land line communication.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Text Content
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Textual material, or a pointer to a resource providing textual material. May be accompanied by basic information about its source and relationship to the source.
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Exactly one of sub-attributes onlineResource or information must be completed in one instance of textContent. Product specifications may restrict the use or content of onlineResource for security. For example, a product specification may forbid populating onlineResource. Product specification authors must consider whether applications using the data product may be prevented from accessing off-system resources by security policies.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Clearance Fixed
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The vertical clearance measured from the horizontal plane towards a fixed (non-opening) feature overhead.
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Vertical clearance fixed must not be used to populate authorized safe clearances.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Uncertainty
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the vertical accuracy of depths, heights, vertical distances and vertical clearances.
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Encodes the vertical uncertainty associated with any vertical measurement.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Zone of Confidence
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The overall indication of the quality of bathymetric data within an area based on the positional accuracy, survey equipment and coverage; optionally within a specified data range.

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: Component of
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: A pointer to the aggregate in a whole-part relationship.

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: Consists of
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: A pointer to a part in a whole-part relationship.

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: Information provided for
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: A pointer to a specific feature(s) for which further information is required.

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: Provides information
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: A pointer to an object that provides more information about the referencing feature or information type.

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: Applies in location
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: The location in which the information item applies

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: The RxN
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: The regulation, restriction, recommendation, or nautical information

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationAssociation.S100FC:name: Additional information
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationAssociation.S100FC:definition: A feature association for the binding between at least one instance of a geo feature and an instance of an information type.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationAssociation.S100FC:name: Associated RxN
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationAssociation.S100FC:definition: Association between a geographic location and a regulation, restriction, recommendation, or nautical information

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureAssociation.S100FC:name: Pilotage District Association
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureAssociation.S100FC:definition: A feature association for the binding between a pilotage district and its component pilot boarding places.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:name: Information Type
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:definition: Generalized information type which carries all the common attributes

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:name: AbstractRxN
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:definition: An abstract superclass for information types that encode rules, recommendations, and general information in text or graphic form.
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:remarks: Subtypes of AbstractRxN carry the same attributes, but differ in the nature of information they encode. There are currently four such subtypes: Regulations, Restrictions, Recommendations, and NauticalInformation.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:name: Contact Details
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:definition: Information on how to reach a person or organisation by postal, internet, telephone, telex and radio systems.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:name: Recommendations
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:definition: Recommendations for a related area or facility.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:name: Regulations
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:definition: Regulations for a related area or facility.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:name: Nautical Information
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:definition: Nautical information about a related area or facility.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Feature Type
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: Generalized feature type which carries all the common attributes.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Organization Contact Area
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A feature often associated with contact information for an organization that exercises a management role or offers a service in the location.
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:remarks: It is not a requirement that every instance of the feature be associated with a management, reporting, or service organization.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Data Coverage
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A geographical area that describes the coverage and extent of spatial objects.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Quality of Bathymetric Data
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An area within which a uniform assessment of the quality of the bathymetric data exists.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Quality of Non-Bathymetric Data
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An area within which a uniform assessment of the quality of the non-bathymetric data exists.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Berth
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A place, generally named or numbered, where a vessel may moor or anchor.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Caution Area
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: Generally, an area where the mariner has to be made aware of circumstances influencing the safety of navigation.
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:remarks: This may be required to identify: a danger, a risk, a rule, or advice -- which is not directly related to a specific object.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Crane
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A machine for lifting, shifting and lowering objects or materials by means of a swinging boom or with a lifting apparatus supported on an overhead track.
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:remarks: The position of a sheerlegs or a travelling crane is defined as its resting position.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Harbour Area (Administrative)
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: The area over which a harbour authority has jurisdiction.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Harbour Facility
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A harbour installation with a service or commercial operation of public interest.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Information Area
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An area for which general information regarding navigation, but not directly related to safety of navigation, is available.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Pilot Boarding Place
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A location offshore where a pilot may board a vessel in preparation to piloting it through local waters.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Pilotage District
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An area within which a pilotage direction exists. Such directions are regulated by a competent harbour authority which dictates circumstances under which they apply.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Restricted Area Navigational
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: A specified area on land or water designated by an appropriate authority within which access or navigation is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions. A navigational restricted area is an area where the restrictions have a direct impact on the navigation of a vessel in the area.
